Iraqi forensic teams have described how they wept as they began to excavate 12 graves
believed to be the final resting place of as many as 1,700 soldiers killed in cold blood by ISIS last summer
The teams began the gruesome task of uncovering the bodies of the young army recruits of Camp Speicher
slaughtered by the Sunni ISIS militants as they surged across northern Iraq for the
days after Islamic State 's fighters were driven from the city by Iraqi forces and Shi'ite paramilitaries
